list.name: Changes
list.comment:
Refactor progress bar update logic and clean up duplicated code
Enhanced progress bar update by modifying the calculation and update logic. Now, it accurately calculates the progress as a percentage and stores it as an integer, improving performance. This update applies across multiple files. Redundant code lines were also eliminated for a cleaner, more readable code.

MESSAGE.value: Add scripts for TMA table validation, structure fixes, migrations, and testing. Include SQL and Python utilities for improved data processing and compatibility.

Add `insert_media_to_entity_values` method and improve ID type handling in `pyarchinit_db_manager.py`. Include updates for maintaining SQLite compatibility and add GIS log for data loading and graph building.

Extend TMA functionality: add media handling, enhance UI with media and map previews, implement thesaurus-based dropdowns, refine signal management, and update material data processing with improved debugging and error handling.
Add scripts for TMA table management: creation, validation, fixing foreign keys, and restructuring. Include utilities for thesaurus cleanup, record migration, and SQLite compatibility verification.
Enhance TMA functionality: implement new print dialog with filtering options, support for "Cronologia" field in dropdowns, and PDF generation for filtered TMA lists.
Update TMA UI: add "List" button and set default tab to "Identificazione"
Add `test_tma_save.py`: initial test script for TMA save functionality

Expand TMA functionality to handle new "TMA - Materiali Ripetibili" table, implement enhanced material data processing with thesaurus-based dropdowns, update data retrieval methods for delegate items, and improve debugging/logging for materials table changes.

Refactor TMA record handling: replace `rec_num` with `n` for better readability, enhance logging for navigation methods, prevent overwriting counters in `set_rec_counter`, improve UI updates, and reload data after material save.

Simplify TMA UI by removing unused buttons and toolbars, disable map preview, and clean up deprecated GUI elements. Refactor material association logic to handle materials as distinct entries with enhanced filtering and export capabilities. Integrate new PDF generation logic and revise workflow for printing single and filtered TMA records.
Add scripts for TMA data processing: thesaurus cleanup, Excel import, PostgreSQL updates, and hierarchy maintenance
Update TMA UI: reorganize layout, enhance dropdown functionality, add export button, and refine tooltips for better clarity.
Add utility scripts and backup files for TMA data processing, debugging, cleanup, and validation.

Update TMA UI layout: adjust grid positions for export button, set "Identificazione" tab as default, and reorganize field mapping in pyarchinit_db_manager. Improve session handling with enhanced commit debugging and rollback functionality.
Update `.idea` files: add new issue navigation links, adjust GitHub settings, and configure new Python test scripts for Excel insert operations
Update `.idea` files: adjust run configurations, update temporary tasks, and improve script selection for Python test scripts
Update `.idea` files: adjust run configurations, modify Python script references, and update properties content formatting
Change `nr_cassa` field type from `INTEGER` to `TEXT` across multiple tables and update related migrations, representations, and metadata.

Refactor label generation and PDF components: remove unused sections, enhance table styling with responsive widths, add excavation year extraction, group records by box number for detailed labels, and update TMA data handling with additional attributes.

Add QR code generation with color customization and minimal QR label style. Include new UI option for "QR Minimal" label style, extend PDF generation, update TMA data handling, and enhance label design logic for improved clarity. Adjust dependencies and modules for QR code support.

Refactor `pyarchinit_tma_label_pdf.py`: enhance QR code generation logic, introduce predefined and hash-based color customization for site names, improve area symbol drawing with detailed mappings, and streamline label layout for better readability and fallback handling.

Refactor TMA components and database operations: improve metadata refresh after updates, enhance table migrations with backup and validation, simplify PDF section structures, and streamline module dependency loading with `requirements.txt` fallback.
Refactor TMA materials table initialization: streamline thesaurus setup, optimize delegate configuration, simplify table and field updates, and enhance language handling for thesaurus values.

Enhance TMA UI and PDF generation: add font size customization for list printing, improve table cell styling with dynamic font size handling, and optimize column widths for landscape A4. Update `Inv_Materiali` to load area values dynamically based on thesaurus.
Update `.idea` files: refine run configurations, adjust script references, and improve year extraction logic in `Periodizzazione.py`.
